One infuriating problem is losing very long journal entries by getting timed out long before the time out feature is reached. This also brings up another issue: A bookkeeper should not have to be timed out as he/she is to work for not only 8 hours but many times they need to work on spreadsheets or other documents and come back to QBO to complete the work. If they should have 10 tabs open as this is a "Multitasking" world, even refreshing a screen after you resign in, does not bring them back to what they were doing. They have to redo all the work again to get back to where they were.; 

A technical issue I have found for this premature kicking out is something to do with Cache. Every now and then you need to empty the entire contents of the browsing history in Chrome. I do not know if this is only a Chrome issue or if it is seen among other OSs or browsers but I have heard of similar issues by several people.

I have submitted many help requests but always get the typical responses of - "Delete the cache". This does not help anyone while working on a 1 hour journal entry. Bookkeeper's Nightmare and
